cs.OS, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the challenges of managing memory accesses and interrupts in modern heterogeneous multicore computers, which are core topics in operating systems (cs.OS), architecture (cs.AR), and systems (cs.SY). The paper also proposes a formal model for addressing these challenges, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
